So, for anyone who is in Accelerated Chemistry, here are the answers to the questions assigned for tonight.  I think they are actually right, and I will try to include steps that lead to the answer along with the answer its self.

Notation - (number) is the charge.  A number after an element is the number of them (subscript).  And of course the number before a compound or element is the coefficient for that item.

38.  a)  MnO4 + ClO2 --> MnO2 + ClO4
Mn(+7)O4(-2 ea) + Cl(+3)O2(-2 ea) --> Mn(+4)O2(-2 ea) + Cl(+7)O4(-2 ea)

Oxidation:
4e(-) + ClO2 --> ClO4
4e(-) + 4OH + ClO2 --> ClO4 + 2H2O

Reduction:
MnO4 --> MnO2 + 3e(-)
MnO4 + 2H2O --> MnO2 + 4OH + 3e(-)

The common multiplier for each is the other.  i.e. - Multiply the 4e(-) in the Oxidation by 3, and the 3e(-) in the Reduction by 4 so that both are 12, and can then cancel.

(4e(-) + 4OH + ClO2 --> ClO4 + 2H2O) * 3
12OH + 3ClO2 --> 3ClO4 + 6H2O

(MnO4 + 2H2O --> MnO2 + 4OH + 3e(-)) * 4
4MnO4 + 8H2O --> 4MnO2 + 16OH

The final answer then, after subtracting like compounds from both sides is:
4MnO4 + 3ClO2 + 2H2O --> 4MnO2 + 3ClO4 + 4OH

Okay, that took forever to type, so I'm just going to type out the answers that I got for the rest of them, if you need any help on a specific one, just ask me, I'm happy to help.

b)  10OH + 2Cr(3+) + 3ClO(-) --> 5H2O + 2CrO4(2+) + 3Cl(-)
c)  6OH + I(-) + 6Mn(3+) --> 6Mn(2+) + IO3(-) + 3H2O

39.  Okay, I am going to try and make a chart for this, if it doesn't work then tough.  The pattern is Ox then Red for each question.

                Element | Agent | Question |
Oxidation     Cl          Mn          (a)     
Reduction     Mn        Cl            (a)     
Ox                N          Cu           (b)
Red              Cu         N             (b)
Ox                P          N              (c)
Red              N          P               (c)
Ox               Sn         Bi              (d)
Red              Bi         Sn              (d)
Ox               Cr         Cl              (e)
Red             Cl          Cr             (e)
Ox               I            V              (f)
Red             V            I               (f)


41.  Since I'm really lazy and I have to eat dinner like... now, all I'm gonna post for this one is the coefficients, since that's what you have to figure out.
a) 1 4 1 1 2
b) 1 4 1 2 2
c) 3 5 2 5 3
d) 2 3 2 3 3
e) 2 3 2 2 3 1
f) 1 2 2 1 2 1 1

And there you have it, I hope this helps someone.

-Chris

So, I just spent about 30 minutes coming up with this little poem.  I have to turn it in tomorrow, and I need to make some revisions, tell me what you think.

Soul Song

A master of beautiful tone
The boy enters a trance
Among the multitude he is alone
Beginning without a glance
His concentration is unbroken
As a songbird on a spring morning
The melody is a heavenly token
Springing from the soul without warning
The harmonics erupt like a volcano
Billowing in unearthly beauty

The boy lives for the thrill
The thrill of winning the game
A simple game played by simple people
The boy runs like the wind
Never tiring
He is there because his heart is there
Nothing can take this away
Being the best is of no importance
All that matters is that the game goes on

The diamond in the rough
A jewel for all eyes to behold
Passion like an inferno
In all things a competitor
Eyes sparkling like the stars above
Features in wonderful compliment
The fruits of the spirit abound
Completing the inner perfection
The boy has met his match

I have of late been thinking about nifty little things that would make people's lives easier.  The one thing that I just thought about right now, which would pretty much solve all the problems of the world would be some kind of thing that allowed someone to focus perfectly on something.  If that was possible, then everything would be much better, and the side effect could be that it cures lazyness.  Those two problems are a few that I have.  If I was half as lazy as I am now, I totally would have 'A's on all my classes, and I would not have missed that stupid test qualification by 2 points.  There are a few things that suck worse than everything, take for intance the fact that I am a nerd.  The only thing wrong with that is that I fail at being a nerd, and there is no way in hell that the label will every leave me.  I wish I was good at things.  I wish I was good at oboe, but I never practice, so I will never get good.  I need to go running with people, I think I will force my parents to let me stay after school, if only I had a ride home...  I wish I wasn't fat.  I hate not being in shape.  Oh well, I wish I could turn my mental strength into physical strength, cause I can learn so much easier than I can work out.  This entry might be my re-entry into the world of LJ.  But, it is not very likely, cause I really don't update very often.  I need to be more active, and not sit in my room online all the time.  I need an ipod, that never runs out of batteries.  Oh well, I want... I need... What I really must do is make do with what I have, and use it to it's full potential.

First of all, Merry Christmas, this has been one of the first Christmas' that I have been truly happy.  I have a hunch why that might be, and I know that it is because of the people that surround me.  My pre-holiday activities were a blast.  I have been ordered to have a party in July celbrating Christmas (ask Will...) so look forward to something like that but only if someone reminds me because there is no way that I will remember.

So, I watched Spiderman 2 today.  Ya, it's an okay movie, but it made me realize something very important about my life.  I realize this is totally cliche, and that everyone probably realizes this, but I am going to point it out anyway.  Candice, I know you are going to say something like, "Well I'm glad your happy."  Or something gloomy like that.  Cheer up everyone!  There is far too much sadness here.  Okay, so to my stupid little thing.  Movies are based upon a person who has conflicting interests, and there is great strife, and then somehow, miraculusly, the interests become aligned, the badguys are defeated, and everyone is happy.  The only reason that we watch movies is so that we can see how our lives could be in a perfect world.  The problem is, the movies are not perfects worlds, there are still "bad" people.  Those people do not go away, becuase there are always sequals to movies.  The thing taht is different in life, is that we do not have to save the whole world by ourselves, we only have to save our smaller worlds, the larger the "world" that you save, the better you are.  If everyone were to work toegether, again, a movie setting, the entire world would be incorperated into the saving, and everyone would truly be better off.  This does not have to be wishful thinking, yet it is.  Again, all the cynical comments will be flowwing, but you know what, if we were to try to do this, even a little, again we would be better.  I feel like my "seperate" interests have become alive as one.  I feel like I'm living a movie.  I am loving every moment of it, I believe that this is truly what the holiday spirit is about.  I wish the past weeks would forever be repeated.

Peace on Earth?
-Chris...

Ya, so here we are again.  I dislike writing essays.  I also dislike tests involving paragraphs.  Kyle: The Dilling test was hella easy.  I don't know what your talking about, but I finished in like, 30 minutes.  I am really looking forward to not only this weekend, but the chance of snow, and also the holidays in general.  I really hope it does NOT snow during christmas, because I am going to be in Florida.  I think were going to Universal Studios, but mabey not.  The important part is, I am going to basking in the sun, and playing in the warm surf, while you suckers who stay home are going to be stuck in the dreary Seattle weather.  Ya, I actually am not going to be gone that long (try to contain your dissapointment) but, it will be an awesome vacation.

I am actually getting to go places and do things this year, first, beginning with the aforementioned vacation, then at Spring Break, the band is going to Disneyland.  This is one of the driving forces behind me being in band.  Then in the summer, I get to tour Eastern Europe for 15 days as part of my orchestra's European Tour.  We are performing in Berlin, and all these awesome, uber good places.  I think that next year, and the end of this year are going to be a blast.

Now, to the not so good, ya, well at the moment there isn't much that I can think of.  So, thats amazing, I am in a permenant good mood as of now, and I am loving every moment of it.  I think I am going to make some peppermint fudge, and for all of you that think its going to be bad, sucks for you, more for me.  Ya, and I am going to be making a bunch of it for my orchestra because I am a nice person, and ya, there should be a bunch left over.

I need to do some christmas shopping, I don't really know why I am putting this in here, but thats okay.  I have no secrets.  Seriously, if you took all the people that I confide in, and put their knowledge together, you could create a database that would know me better than I know myself.  That is really scary.  Anywho, I think that I am going to go shopping like, soon.  So, I need some ideas for what some people want, I obviously cannot buy for everyone, so if you actually read this, then speak up, you may be lucky.

I have now pretty much run out of ideas for what to talk about, so I may just ramble on about nothing for a while, I do that a lot.  I need to fix that actually, but its a really bad habit.  I can talk to you forever about nothing, but it will sound like something, until you actually think about it.  What is interesting is that since I do that, I can tell sometimes when other people are doing it.  Take the presidential debates for example, GeeDubya said a lot of nothing a lot of times.  It was really sad, because he would say variations of the same but of nothing to like, 5 questions in a row.  I was laughing on the inside, yet, crying also, because I knew that teh chances of him being elected were high.

Ya, so it would suck to live in Russia.  We are complaining, with good reason about our current elected official, but we need to take a step back and look at the bigger picture.  Russia for example is slipping, not very slowly back into a Czar-ship.  Their elected "president" has taken much power away from them, and has destroyed the checks and balances system that was put in place when the democracy was put into place.  I am actually concerned about the people there, and what this could mean for the world's stage.  I doubt that the White House knows anything about it, nor cares about the rest of the world, but we the educated, soon to be voting person's of America should know.  If any of you come across major world events, such as this, please tell me about them, I like to know what is happening in our world.  It makes my arguing contests so much easier (sarcasm).  Also, I think its really sad when people do not catch other people's sarcasm, especially when the people in question are good friends.

Well, you will have to wait till I eventually get around to writing here again to see about what I have experienced in my life.  Expect another installment at least by the end of Friday, cause I have a soccer game, and I will likely post the results of that, I do not know if I will post anymore before then though.

~Christopher

Ya, Will Yost is my favorite person for today.  I made some fudge with my Ghiradelli's dark chocolate chips, which are on sale at Safeway by the way. Holy hell that stuff is good.  It's so rich that... ya, it's good.  It is also really easy to make.  Yum, Yum, YUM!.

So... today... the parade.  I have decided that doughnut stealing people should be shot, and I swear to god if anyone else takes a box of doughnuts from me, I will kill them.  Allow me to explain, we were marching along the parade rout, which was long, and I was sweating more than I have ever before in my life.  I was about to my limit, because there was no reward that I could see.  Then, this nice parade person, who was in the parade, who was also giving away free boxes of Krispy Kreme Doughnuts.  You know, where there is like 10 boxes, and you are always the next person after they run out, well not today, I got a box of doughnuts.  I was overjoyed, I was dancing to the music, there was a spring in my step, and everything was going to be okay.  I had something to look forward to.  Then, horror of all horrors, the Sonics mascot goes over to me, takes the box of scrumptious doughnuts, from between me and my drum, and throws my hopes, my motivation, my reward, into the crowd.  I see it dissapear into the mob of spectators.  You should have seen my face, and you probably did not want to know what I said.  Fortunatley for him, I was marching, and the tv crews were moving the cameras onto my section at that time, otherwise, I would have rained down hellfire and death in the form of drumsticks and a 75 pound bass drum.  What I want to know is if they got that on tv, because if they did not pick up my vocal, I think that they would replay it a buch, and that would be totally worth it.  I would be famous!

So, afterward, we went to the best noodle place in the world, ZAO.  I had something called "simply chicken" which is like a Thai version of chicken noodle soup.  Let me tell you, it was amazing.  I ate till I was full, and was still absorbed in the goodness of the taste, and kept eating.  I left with the content over-fullness that you have after an excellent meal.  We then walked around in the brisk morning air, and it was cool.  I was all tired by then, and we went home.  Then I made fudge.

Now I am here, thinking about a certain someone who is hopefully having fun in Tacoma now, doing what I believe is called PRC.  I don't really know what that is, but she enjoys it, so it must be cool.  Ya, and I saw The Day After Tomorrow today, and it's a pretty good movie, its nice and cute with a happy, cliche ending.  But the pretense is frightenly possible.  Stuff that makes you think.  Yup, and if any of you have seen National Treasure, I want to know if it's a good movie, I have heard good things about it, and I think I'm gonna see it next weekend.  So, if you ruin the movie, you get no fudge.

Words of Wisdom - "Decide what you want, and go for it, no matter what the risk, no matter what other people say, and no matter what the cost." - uh, someone paraphrased by me.

~ Me = Chris A Shank

Ya, so as I'm writing this I have a migraine, and I almost threw up a few minutes ago.  Trust me, its not fun spending like, 5 minutes on your knees in front of the toilet, because I might throw up.  God I hate being sick.  Ya, I think I know why I got the migraine, and the reason is not public enough to put here, but I will say that some very stressful things happened last night, and I got through them, but I think I beat myself up at night or something because I woke up with a bruise in my wenis, and on my arm.  Ya, if anyone knows how to get rid of a sickness, please enlighten me.  My vision goes blurry every once in a while, and I can't see out of one side of my eye, I also have an ensanely bad headache.  I'm on the usual drugs, so dont suggest that.

We had a soccer game on Tuesday, we scored first, something that has never been done to the team we played.  We lost by a healthy margin, but that was not the point, not only did we score, but we held them to the smallest amount of points yet.  We nearly had about 4 other goals, but alas, Fabian is an amazing goal keeper.  We played the team sponsored by Sports World, and when I went into the store yesterday, the owner of the store, who watched our game, and who is like almost a family friend, told me that I should be playing on a select team.  I guess thats good, I dont really know what I'm gonna do come next soccer season.  I really need to get out and do some conditioning though.

Chelsea - I think we have made it through the worst, and the road to recovery is clear, can we please not let things go so long next time?  I think that what took place last night, talking to you, was why I got a migrain.  I really did not want to do what I did, but now, after doing it and getting some sleep, besides the migrain, I feel better.  We reached a new level of open-ness, and lets please try to keep it that way.

Turkey day - Well, I woke up, and went and played some soccer at Bear Creek Elementary School.  The field there sucks, but thats okay because this was just a fun time to mess around.  We had a bunch of people there, around 48.  It was awesome, beating what seems like hundreds of smaller children at soccer will never get boring.  Especially going around, through, but NOT over my brothers teacm mates, and then the adults, and scoring, there is something sweet about that accomplishment.  The feeling of scoring by yourself, and knowing that you have just instilled fear into the other team is greatly diminished by kicking the ground so hard that you can hardly walk.  I did this, so both feet, that is why I have practically vowed to never play on wet sand fields again.  I felt almost like I fractured my foot or something, but I think its okay now.  After two hours of soccer, we came home, via Safeway, and I got the ingredients for some delectible fudge.  If you saw our orange volkswagon bus driving around, you can take pride in knowing its driver (me).  Then we had an amazing dinner, turkey, mashed potatoes, the works.  Followed up with some fresh pumpkin pie, some blackberry pie, and there was mince pie, but I dont like that.  After that, we just sort of hung around our house and talked.  My migrain set in, and I because a recluse.

NOW - Interspursed with nausia, and times when I cannot see at all, I am doing pretty good, my nagging headache is really annoying, and the drugs I took for it are not working at all.  So, I am going to stop for now, I need to be better about updating here, because it makes me reflect on the days events, and thats a good thing.

Peace out
~Chris
